label.value: abolished protein localization to pericentric heterochromatin during mitosis

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to pericentric heterochromatin is abolished during mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: mononucleate vegetative cell with mislocalized septum and anucleate compartment

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell contains a single nucleus and an asymmetrically located septum. The septum divides the cell into two compartments, one of which contains the nucleus.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K9 trimethylation at heterochromatin island at meiotic gene during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which trimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 is decreased at heterochromatin islands near genes that are normally expressed during the meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromatin at heterochromatin island at meiotic gene during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the maintenance of localization of a protein at a location in heterochromatin at heterochromatin islands occurs to a lower extent than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased nucleosome occupancy

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleosome occupancy is higher than normal at one or more specific sites. Nucleosome occupancy measures the tendency for DNA in a given region to be packaged into nucleosomes.

label.value: increased nucleosome occupancy at transcription start site

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleosome occupancy is higher than normal at transcription start sites. Nucleosome occupancy measures the tendency for DNA in a given region to be packaged into nucleosomes.

label.value: decreased protein localization to linear element at meiotic recombination hotspot

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to linear elements is decreased at one or more meiotic recombination hotspots.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: shmoo with flat tip

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a cell forms a mating projection with a flatter (less rounded) tip than normal.

label.value: variable cell size at division with subsequent division at normal size

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which cells in a population do not divide at a uniform size, although each cell divides to form equal-size daughter cells, which then subsequently divide at a normal size. Within one population, some cells may be larger and others smaller than normal (i.e. compared to wild-type cells under the same conditions) upon the first division. Daughter cells that are larger than normal upon formation divide earlier, and smaller-formed daughter cells divide later, than cells formed at a normal size.

label.value: variable cell size at division with subsequent division at abnormal size

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which cells in a population do not divide at a uniform size, although each cell divides to form equal-size daughter cells, which then subsequently divide at an abnormal size. Within one population, some cells may be larger and others smaller than normal (i.e. compared to wild-type cells under the same conditions) upon each division.

label.value: normal protein localization to kinetochore during meiotic metaphase I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the kinetochore of a chromosome is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during metaphase of meiosis I.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to kinetochore during meiotic anaphase I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the kinetochore of a chromosome does not occur during anaphase of the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to kinetochore during meiosis II

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the kinetochore of a chromosome does not occur during the second meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: mononucleate monoseptate vegetative cell with anucleate compartment

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell contains one nucleus and one septum. The septum divides the cell into two compartments, one of which contains the nucleus.

definition.value: Most mononucleate monoseptate cells are inviable (cf. FYPO:0002303), and the viable cells (FYPO:0007665) are diploid.

label.value: viable mononucleate monoseptate vegetative cell with anucleate compartment

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is viable, and contains one nucleus and one septum. The septum divides the cell into two compartments, one of which contains the nucleus.

label.value: normal establishment or maintenance of actin cytoskeleton polarity during mating

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the establishment or maintenance of actin cytoskeleton polarity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during conjugation with cellular fusion.

label.value: increased protein localization to shmoo tip

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the tip of a shmoo, or mating projection, is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: elongated vegetative cell with cell cycle arrest in mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a vegetative cell is elongated and progression through the mitotic cell cycle is arrested in G1 phase.

label.value: viable swollen vegetative cell with complete DNA rereplication

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is viable, has a larger volume than normal, and undergoes one or more rounds of rereplication of the entire genome. In a swollen cell, both length and diameter may be greater than normal, although the cell is only considered elongated if the length:diameter ratio is also greater than normal.

label.value: inviable mononucleate monoseptate vegetative cell with anucleate compartment and normal cell length

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is inviable, is normal length, and has one nucleus and one septum. The septum divides the cell into two compartments, one of which contains the nucleus.

label.value: normal transcription scaling

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the coordination of transcription rates to scale linearly with cell size is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Transcriptional scaling maintains biomolecule concentrations as cells grow and divide. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be measured.

label.value: transcription scaling with nuclear size decoupled from cell size

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate of transcription scales linearly with nuclear size instead of total cell size. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

label.value: abolished invertase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which invertase activity (beta-fructofuranosidase activity) is absent.

label.value: increased invertase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of invertase activity (beta-fructofuranosidase activity) is increased.

label.value: abolished cell population growth on sucrose carbon source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which a cell population does not grow in a medium containing sucrose as the carbon source.

definition.value: Use this term for a population of cells that does not grow with sucrose as the carbon source, but does grow using a different carbon source (a cell population that does not grow on any media would be considered inviable). Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: normal intracellular sterol transport

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the directed movement of sterols within cells is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abnormal sterol distribution

value.value: A localization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of sterols in cellular membranes is abnormal.

label.value: normal sterol distribution

value.value: A localization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of sterols in cellular membranes is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased replication fork arrest at RTS1 barrier

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which replication fork arrest at the RTS1 barrier (normally located in the mating-type region) occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased ribonucleotide incorporation into DNA

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which more ribonucleotides than normal are incorporated into one or both strands during mitotic DNA replication.

label.value: abnormal RNA-DNA hybrid ribonuclease activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate or other catalytic property of a RNA-DNA hybrid ribonuclease activity is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal cortical polarity patch dynamics during mating

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which assembly, exploratory movement, or disassembly of the Cdc42-containing cortical polarity patch is abnormal during mating.

label.value: wide actin fusion focus

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which components of the actin fusion focus are more widely distributed along the shmoo tip than normal.

label.value: increased level of early meiotic gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA transcribed from early meiotic genes measured in a cell is higher than normal (i.e. higher than observed in wild-type cells during vegetative growth). Early meiotic genes are normally transcribed during pre-meiotic S phase and recombination.

label.value: increased vegetative cell population growth during nutrient starvation

value.value: A cell growth phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is increased relative to normal under conditions of starvation for one or more nutrients.

label.value: increased number of nuclear exosome foci

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the cell contains more nuclear exosome foci than normal.

label.value: normal protein localization to nuclear exosome focus during meiosis

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to nuclear exosome foci is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during meiosis. Nuclear exosome foci, also called Mmi1 foci, are small structures that form within the nucleus, and contain proteins involved in degrading meiosis-specific RNAs during the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to kinetochore during meiotic metaphase I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the kinetochore of a chromosome does not occur during metaphase of the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal cell growth polarization

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells can grow in a normally (i.e. as in wild type) polarized manner as in the presence of a polarity landmark. The landmark itself may be in a normal or abnormal location.

definition.value: The difference between this term and 'normal cell polarity' (FYPO:0005456) is that this term can be used if a polarity landmark is in an abnormal place, but polar growth takes place at the landmark. FYPO:0005465 can be used only when all aspects of polar growth are normal.

label.value: catalytic activity regulator phenotype

value.value: A phenotype that affects a molecular function which in turn binds to an enzyme and thereby directly regulates its catalytic activity.

label.value: normal DNA strand exchange activator activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the activity of a DNA strand exchange activator is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased DNA strand exchange activator activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the activity of a DNA strand exchange activator is increased.

label.value: decreased DNA strand exchange activator activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the activity of a DNA strand exchange activator is decreased.

label.value: abolished DNA strand exchange activator activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the activity of a DNA strand exchange activator is absent.

label.value: normal DNA strand exchange inhibitor activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the activity of a DNA strand exchange inhibitor is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased DNA strand exchange inhibitor activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the activity of a DNA strand exchange inhibitor is increased.

label.value: decreased DNA strand exchange inhibitor activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the activity of a DNA strand exchange inhibitor is decreased.

label.value: abolished DNA strand exchange inhibitor activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the activity of a DNA strand exchange inhibitor is absent.

label.value: decreased frequency of conjugation with non-sister cells

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a smaller than normal proportion of cells in a homothallic population undergoes conjugation with non-sister cells.

label.value: inviable small vegetative cell with premature mitotic G2/M phase transition

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a vegetative cell is inviable and an abnormally low volume, and in which the G2/M transition of the mitotic cell cycle begins earlier than normal.
